# Example environment for PepperWizard. Copy to `.env` (gitignored) and adjust.
# docker compose reads this file automatically.

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Compose-file chain. Determines which services start and which overlays apply
# when you run plain `docker compose up` (no -f flags).
#
# On hosts with an NVIDIA GPU + nvidia-container-runtime, enable GPU STT by
# including the GPU overlay:
#
#   COMPOSE_FILE=docker-compose.yml:docker-compose.gpu.yml
#
# When developing against sibling repos (../PepperBox, ../PepperPerception),
# also append the dev overlay:
#
#   COMPOSE_FILE=docker-compose.yml:docker-compose.gpu.yml:docker-compose.dev.yml
#
# On CPU-only hosts, leave this unset (or just set it to `docker-compose.yml`).
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# COMPOSE_FILE=docker-compose.yml:docker-compose.gpu.yml

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# STT device/compute-type overrides.
#
# The stt-service auto-detects GPU presence by default (STT_DEVICE=auto).
# Use these only to force a specific path — e.g. to debug CPU behaviour on a
# GPU host, or to pin a specific CTranslate2 compute type.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# STT_DEVICE=cuda
# STT_COMPUTE_TYPE=float16

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# HuggingFace offline mode (stt-service).
#
# Whisper weights live in a named docker volume (huggingface-cache) so they
# survive container recreation. Defaults are HF_HUB_OFFLINE=0 and
# TRANSFORMERS_OFFLINE=0 — so swapping model_size in pepper_wizard/config/stt.json
# to an uncached model automatically downloads it into the persistent volume
# on the next restart. Startup cost when cache is warm: one small HEAD request
# to HuggingFace (~100-300ms).
#
# Set both to 1 to harden the service against HuggingFace Hub outages or
# rate-limit stalls — but the cache must be pre-populated with every model
# you might use, because offline mode blocks downloads entirely:
#
#   HF_HUB_OFFLINE=1
#   TRANSFORMERS_OFFLINE=1
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# HF_HUB_OFFLINE=1
# TRANSFORMERS_OFFLINE=1
